						<div class="postbody">Here's some things that I immediately see:<br /><br />1- Don't leave the old stubs (from &quot;reset&quot; through &quot;nmi&quot;) in your code). They're misleading (and currently horrifically wrong)<br />2- You need to wait two vblanks before you start writing to any PPU register: see <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_power_up_state">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_power_up_state</a><!-- m --></div>

